President Trump and Chairman Kim held a historic meeting at the DMZ (Demilitarized Zone) between North and South Korea. Chairman Kim expressed surprise at the meeting, stating that it was not prearranged and that he was notified of Trump's willingness to meet late the previous day. He emphasized the symbolic significance of the meeting place, which represents the separation between the two Koreas and their shared unfortunate past. Chairman Kim expressed his desire to use their strong relationship to create positive opportunities and improve relations between the two countries. President Trump thanked Chairman Kim for showing up, as it would have reflected poorly on him if he hadn't. He praised the power of Chairman Kim's voice and their developed relationship, stating that it has made a positive impact on many people. President Trump expressed honor and appreciation for being asked to step over the line into North Korea, calling it a great and historic meeting. The meeting concluded with both leaders expressing their gratitude and satisfaction.